```{r}
cat("Model Performance Insights:\n")
cat("‚úî Manual SARIMA has the **lowest MAPE**, indicating the best forecast accuracy on test data.\n")
cat("‚úî Auto ARIMA also performs well, but not as well as SARIMA.\n")
cat("‚úî Holt-Winters shows the **highest MAPE**, suggesting it underperforms compared to ARIMA models.\n")
cat("‚úî The Ljung-Box p-values for all models are > 0.05, implying residuals are likely white noise (good model fit).\n")

```


```{r}
cat("üîé Forecast Comparison Implications:\n")
cat("- While all models predict a similar **upward trend**, the **forecasted values differ subtly**.\n")
cat("- Manual SARIMA is more conservative and smoother; Auto ARIMA fluctuates more.\n")
cat("- Holt-Winters tends to smooth aggressively, possibly missing local variations.\n")
cat("- Use-case matters: For **strategic forecasting**, SARIMA is most stable. For **short-term alerts**, Auto ARIMA might be more sensitive.\n")

```


```{r}
cat("üìå Recommendations:\n")
cat("- ‚úÖ Use **Manual SARIMA** for official forecasts (lowest MAPE & reliable residuals).\n")
cat("- üîÑ Continue monitoring forecast accuracy with incoming data (update models quarterly).\n")
cat("- üìà Visualize forecasts monthly and assess trends versus actuals.\n")
cat("- üõ†Ô∏è Optionally ensemble ARIMA + Holt-Winters for robustness.\n")

